Over the past three months, a new cohort of ASML professionals stepped out of their day-to-day roles and into the fast-moving world of early-stage startups at HighTechXL.

For 1.5 days a week, talents joined forces with deep-tech ventures tackling some of the world‚Äôs toughest challenges.

 üî• Startups offered a fresh perspective, experimentation, and real-world impact.

Along the way, some talents became more proactive,¬†taking initiative, speaking up, and pursuing their own ambitions without waiting for permission. 

Others learned how to delegate more effectively, communicate with clarity and purpose, and align better with the needs of their audience. A few discovered the value of taking a calculated risk now and then. 

Big thanks to the ventures who welcomed this year‚Äôs talents and to the mentors who guided them along the way.

What a day.
What a community.

Last year, we asked you to think big, right here at home.
And at XL Day 2025, we saw what that looks like in action.

With the amazing Robin van Scheijndel leading the day, we went from the rollercoaster stories of Dr. Hamed Sadeghian, CEO of Nearfield Instruments  Instruments, and Hans De Neve, CEO of Carbyon, to the incredible pitches by our latest cohort of ventures, alumni, Singapore teams, and ASML talents.

Each moment reminded us why we do this. Building in deep tech isn‚Äôt easy. But with collaboration, perseverance, and a little irrational optimism, it‚Äôs possible.

A special thanks to the teams who worked hard to be on stage: @High Tech Binders, Galuxea, @Ovalytix, Veridis, Luper Technologies, SonicPrecision, Ailytics, N&E Innovations Pte Ltd, WO:EX Pte Ltd., Gray Matter Solutions.

In the second part of the afternoon, we had three amazing breakout sessions led by Frank Smallegange, guiding us through the Hero‚Äôs Journey; Patricia de Kort, Soukaina Adnane-Murphy, and Michael Stucky, challenging the ventures in the Investors‚Äô Arena; and Luis Pedro Oliveira, H. C.  (Hugo) Leyte, Stefan Kuipers, Aron Vromans, and John Bell leading an interactive panel on SecurityXL.

Right here in this region, we‚Äôre growing a powerhouse. Powered by founders. Backed by brave investors and partners. But we‚Äôre just getting started.

We‚Äôre filled with gratitude for everyone who joined, shared, pitched, supported, and simply showed up with open minds and big dreams. Thank you. üíô

Were you there? We‚Äôd love to hear:
 üëâ What moved you?
 üëâ What stuck with you?

Drop your thoughts in the comments,  we‚Äôd love to hear what you took away from the day.

üåü Great news! We‚Äôre excited to announce that penomo is joining the Rockstart Energy family! ‚ö°

Penomo was founded in 2023 by Jasvir Dhillon and Sascha K. to redefine how renewable infrastructure is financed. Their platform combines sector-specific expertise with tokenization technology, enabling originators, lenders, and investors to manage complex debt workflows seamlessly, from underwriting and structuring to real-time monitoring. By streamlining access to private credit and transforming renewable assets into liquid, tradable instruments, Penomo opens new financing pathways for mid-market projects that are often underserved by traditional institutions. The result: faster, more transparent, and more flexible capital flows that accelerate the global energy transition.

üí¨ Why penomo?
‚ÄúThe ‚Ç¨4.5 trillion energy-transition financing gap is a major bottleneck to climate goals, especially for small to mid-sized renewable infrastructure. Traditional processes are slow, opaque, and structurally unfit for this long-tail. Penomo makes energy infrastructure finance faster and more accessible by combining tokenization, real-time asset monitoring, and AI-driven credit assessment to turn projects into liquid, investable assets delivered through a unified infrastructure credit operating system. We‚Äôre excited to back this commercially and technologically strong team as they unlock the next wave of climate infrastructure through programmable capital and digital asset markets.‚Äù ‚Äì Max ter Horst, Managing Partner of Rockstart Energy

üí¨ Why Rockstart?
‚ÄúRockstart's Energy Fund backs unconventional founders with focus on low-carbon tech with direct backing from the Dutch National Funding Body. It stands out providing more than capital ‚Äì sector-specific ecosystem of mentors, investors and industry partners and a track record of staying on the cap table through Series B. The Rockstart team is very thorough and intentional, we fully aligned on the urgent bold innovation needed in infrastructure finance to address Europe's and the World's energy transition, making it a compelling case for Penomo to be part of its portfolio. We expect the program to help fast-track our GTM and product deployment with feedback on key launches that we may be blind-sided to, access to advisors (internal and external to Rockstart) and potential partners.‚Äù ‚Äì Jasvir Dhillon, Co-founder & CEO of penomo

üöÄ At Rockstart, we back visionary founders tackling the world‚Äôs most pressing challenges. Penomo is unlocking new financing paths for the energy transition, helping channel private capital into the renewable infrastructure powering a sustainable future.

#Rockstart #Penomo #Startups #Founders #Investment #EnergyTransition #Fintech #Energy #Sustainability #Innovation #Impact
